{"TopicId":169633,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Editing fairing size (height) in notepad craft file?","CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-16T03:15:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-16T03:15:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo... I got a massive payload that I want to send into space, it\u0027s not particularly wide, but it\u0027s extremely tall, so tall that I had a difficulty building fairing for it since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E space is not enough for me to build the fairing. Is there any way to edit fairing height by using notepad on craft file? How to do it? And is there a limit of how long I can build it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-16T03:17:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould this help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed145136110\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/162790-131-hangar-extender-extended/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3108515\u0026amp;embedComment=3108515\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3108515\u0022 style=\u0022height:299px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-16T03:35:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223269007\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022169633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221516072535\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ARS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, ARS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any way to edit fairing height by using notepad on craft file? How to do it? And is there a limit of how long I can build it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, easily (more on this later), no.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFind the procedural fairing part. It has a procedural fairing module with some numbers like radius and height. Just edit those and you\u0027re good to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-16T03:53:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223269009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022169633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221516072642\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould this help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7462618747\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/162790-131-hangar-extender-extended/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3108515\u0026amp;embedComment=3108515\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3108515\u0022 style=\u0022height:315px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m already used hangar extender, but it makes me difficult when an extremely tall fairing is mated with launch vehicle since I can\u0027t clearly see the staging parts and adding parts to the rocket\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"boccelounge","CreatedById":155789,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-16T05:17:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock fairings can be as tall as you\u0027d like; your vessel is just too tall to build it. \u00A0This is easy to fix:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Use the Offset Gizmo to drag your Root Part down, so that the fairing base is near the floor of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Build your fairing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Use the Offset Gizmo to drag your Root Part back up, so the bottom of the rocket is above the floor of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. \u003Cs\u003EProfit!\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0Launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHTH, cheers!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}